Package: amatrix.demo
Type: Package
Title: Demonstration of Accelerating a Classic Algorithm with 'amatrix'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Bradley", "Buchsbaum", email = "brad.buchsbaum@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Internal demonstration package for 'amatrix'. Implements
    logistic regression via iteratively reweighted least squares (IRLS)
    with the hot kernels expressed as 'amatrix' operations, so the same
    code runs on plain base matrices (CPU) and on accelerated 'adgeMatrix'
    inputs (GPU backends) without modification. Not intended for release.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.3)
Imports:
    stats,
    amatrix
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    amatrix.mlx
Additional_repositories: https://bbuchsbaum.r-universe.dev
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
